Jan 21 2006	More Tenderloin not Union Square	Had a bad experience with the Clarion Bedford back in a 2001 visit to San Francisco. It was advertised as a three star hotel but as you can see from the pictures, our room was horrible. There were cigarette burns on the furniture, exposed insulation on the rusty pipes in the closet. Chips on the furniture and scuff marks on the walls and doors. The carpets were stained in the room and in the hallway outside our room. Not to mention, we had to walk past prostitutes and vagrants on our way from the Muni to the hotel. I see it is still rated as a three star hotel but after the experience we had, we'll never go back. I eventually got our travel agent to put us in a different hotel but we still wound up having to pay for the one night that we stayed at the Clarion Bedford.	
May 22 2005	Not for everybody website photos misleading.	We were booked to stay here for four days, but ended up staying only one night. Like all Kimpton properties, they have a great pet policy and the price (under $100) was very reasonable. However, we were put in a really dingy room with horrible lighting on the ninth floor.... nothing like the sleek, modern rooms shown on the website. It had that distinct gummy-paint-won't-dry feeling that reminds one of undergraduate apartments. We were there with our dog and found that downtown San Francisco is just not a very easy place to stay with a dog, so we moved out to a suburban hotel. Valet parking was expensive and a hassle, and it's important to note that this was a hangout for GenX types. The rickety elevator and very narrow halls made me think that this would be a deathtrap in a fire. For the hip with budget constraints, not a good choice for families.	
