Sep 27 2004	Clean and comfortable but lacking in amenities	Although the hotel was advertised as having facilities to provide meals, breakfasts, room service and drinks, there is no longer a bar or restaurant at this hotel. This was a disappointment as we were expecting to be able to eat there. Nonetheless, the hotel is really well presented and the staff exceptional. The rooms are clean and tidy and have refreshments but as with any mini bar, the prices are pretty high. The hotel is also quite an uphill walk from Union Square and not necessarily suited to anyone who is elderly or has mobility problems.	
Sep 1 2004	Great Hotel!!	Stayed here this past August 12-15, 2004 and was incredibly delighted with the location, service and ambiance. The staff was helpful and attentive, the location was excellent for walking around the city and it was clean. There was no air conditioning, although it was not needed and street noise could be an issue if it bothers you - I prefer fresh air myself!! We rented an Avis car which was right down the block and did find parking on the street, although it took a couple drives around the block to find a space one night. Great hotel for the price would visit there again!!	
Aug 3 2004	Funky Purple Hotel	After searching through almost all the hotels in San Francisco, I ended up selecting Hotel Cosmo because of the modern &amp; contemporary style I saw on the internet. Upon opening the door though we entered into a room (smoking) not at all like I had seen on the internet. We called the front desk and were switched to a room just as shown in all the pictures. I believe that some or all of the smoking rooms have not yet been renovated so they can be a disappointment. Once we switched I was thoroughly happy though. The bathroom was small, and the nightstands &amp; dresser could be updated a little, but the rest of the decor in the room made up for it. The valet service was a little expensive @ $25 a night, but hey, it's San Fran. The staff was so incredibly nice &amp; willing to make our stay as wonderful as possible. The hotel is within walking distance of many things, but you will need to either take the trolley car or a rental car unless you want to walk some very steep hills to get to your destination. I strongly suggest asking about the room before you book it (if not online). If you want a smoking room &amp; want the one shown on the website ask if it's been renovated.	
