Jul 17 2004	THE COSMO WAS CHARMING	I really enjoyed the hotel. We were on the 16th floor, and the view was really nice. The bathroom was a bit small, but hey, this is Downtown San Francisco, and the hot bath after walking was perfect. The staff was friendly and helpfull, than the staff you would find in the city of Las Vegas, that's for sure. We were close enough to the Cable Car and to Bart that we parked the car and left it for 3 days. The daily parking fee of 25.00 was more than I expected, but then again, people pay that and more in Los Angeles just going to work!!!. And with the parking came unlimited in's and out's. But it was more convenient to walk, or ride the public transportation. (walking was difficult with all the hills though). The staff each morning would take out a map and tell us exactly what we needed to do to get to our destination, and always with a smile. We had a great time, and would recommend this hotel to anyone.	
