Jun 20 2004	We enjoyed our stay. June 2004	All the staff was friendly and helpful. The room and bathroom were a bit smaller than average but were clean and the beds comfortable. The view from the 12th floor was great. They displayed local art work around the lobby which we enjoyed. Although there were no air conditioners, the open window kept the room cool. I am a hot natured person so I called for a fan which sent everyone else in the room running for the additional blankets conveniently left in the closet. There was an honor bar with a small refridgerator but we never used it since there was a convenience store so close.We walked to Chinatown, Union Square and caught the cable car to Fisherman's Wharf. We never felt unsafe, even at night. There were convenience stores, a laundry mat, hair/nail salon, Avis car rental, a coffee shop and several restaurants (some required reservations such as Fena and La Colonial) within a couple blocks. Oh and for our final night since we were so tired, we ordered Pizza Hut (from around the block).We definately enjoyed our stay at the Cosmo hotel and would stay there again.	
