May 13 2004	Our stay at the Cosmo	We stayed at this hotel for a few days in September 2003. My only complaint was the tiny bathrooms/windows that became stuck. My only concern with the open window was that there was no screen. The window opened all the way so it'd be easy for someone to fall out. Not recommended for people with small kids. I loved the view from the 14th floor. Loved the funky, retro-ish manner in which the room was decorated, although I admit that it might not suit some people's style. The staff was extremely friendly. We had no trouble getting around town walking/on buses/cable cars. I believe it was 25 dollars per day for parking, and next time I think I would look around for a cheaper lot as we never used our car during our stay. Never felt unsafe walking around neighborhood at night. Overall, I had a great stay at the Cosmo and I would definitely stay there again!	
May 1 2004	Very comfortable but low on decor	Having been told that the hotel was right next to union square, we were somewhat disappointed to find that it was a steep four block uphill journey. We stayed in a deluxe room on the second highest floor, with a not too bad view of the urban jungle. The room was of a nice size but they had skimped a bit on the bathroom and we only had a few cable channels. It certainly was not as nice as in the photos. Maid service was a bit erratic and it's clearly in need of redecoration. Having said that the room was very very comfortable with a wonderfully soft bed which was just what you needed after a hard day's sightseeing. Good value for money overall, and if you don't plan to spend too much time in the hotel then this is great. There is a free wine hour but it seems like a bit of an afterthought and there is not really enough for even half the guests to have just one glass. Served well by local buses although don't expect the staff to know that.	
Apr 20 2004	Dont believe the pictures	I stayed at the hotel cosmo in spring 2004. Its always a suprise to see how the website photos match up with reality. The lobby looked similar to the photos online but my room was very different. It was a typical ugly motel room. Clean, but by no means the sleak modern look they boast on the web. My guess is only the suites are like that. If your driving, park overnight in the garage one block over, its 18$ for 24 hours as opposed to the $25 plus tax and tip for the hotels valet service (i think they end up parking your car in the same garage anyway). All in all not a bad place to stay just don't expect a good looking room.	
