Mar 25 2004	Quiet 	After trudging up Powell and Post streets dragging 80 lbs of luggage (poor ground transport planning by moi), my friend and I were pleasantly surprised by Hotel Cosmo. The staff were welcoming and accomodating during our stay, the room small and cozy with fabulously comfortable beds and real down pillows. No restaurant in the hotel, but while in San Francisco, who cares? Real opening windows, which we left open for the duration of our stay to enjoy the fresh, cool breezes. The staff told me that the hotel has been recently sold again, and that more improvements will be made (maybe double-glazed windows to cut down on street noise? I hope not - loved the opening windows!). The hotel is far enough away from Union Square to cut down on the street noise, but close enough to walk anywhere...and much better to walk without one's suitcase - LOL! Will definitely be back!	
